1. follow [the official instructions from node js](https://nodejs.org/en/docs/guides/nodejs-docker-webapp/) to create the Dockerfile and .dockerignore
2. navigate to uiserver folder, build docker image: **"sudo docker build -t azureuser/smartpage ."**. Last parameter . indicates source folder is current folder, in case you're running from a different folder.
3. run the docker image file: **"sudo docker run -p 443:8001 -e "PORT=8001" azureuser/smartimage"**. our server.js checks env PORT (process.env.PORT) for the https port, Dockerfile exposes ports 8000-8010, -p 443:8001 means we port external 443 port to docker internal 8001 port, then use -e "PORT=8001" to set PORT env and tell nodejs to listen to 8001 port.
